comment_data.body:
*@devoncarew commented on Oct 28, 2019, 11:56 PM UTC:*

Interesting; re:

```
Invalid argument(s): Only absolute paths are supported: lib\AbstractDataProvider.dart
#0      AnalysisDriver._throwIfNotAbsolutePath (package:analyzer/src/dart/analysis/driver.dart:1698:7)

```

@scheglov - does this mean that we're passing a non-absolute path into `flutter.setSubscriptions` from the IntelliJ plugin?

*@scheglov commented on Oct 29, 2019, 12:34 AM UTC:*

Yes, it looks to me as well that we pass non-absolute path(s) to DAS.

*@devoncarew commented on Oct 29, 2019, 4:40 AM UTC:*

/move flutter/flutter-intellij

*@devoncarew commented on Oct 29, 2019, 4:41 AM UTC:*

@mit-mit - can you re-enable the move bot for this repo?

*@devoncarew commented on Oct 29, 2019, 3:07 PM UTC:*

> Yes, it looks to me as well that we pass non-absolute path(s) to DAS.

OK; cc @jacob314. From looking at the code, we're calling VirtualFile.getCanonicalPath(). I don't see any absolute related APIs. The canonical API may generally return absolute paths except in some circumstances (like light virtual files?). We should either switch to a different API, or guard against sending in non-absolute paths for the outlier files.

cc @alexander-doroshko for clarification about how to get an absoluate path from a VirtualFile.

*@alexander-doroshko commented on Oct 29, 2019, 6:19 PM UTC:*

This may be a temporary in-memory file, HTTP-remote file, file inside a zip, etc. Analysis Server can work only with local files, so I think you should check for `isInLocalFileSystem()` and not send file path to the server if it's not. In Dart plugin we do it in `DartAnalysisServerService#isLocalAnalyzableFile()`.

*@alexander-doroshko commented on Oct 29, 2019, 6:43 PM UTC:*

@devoncarew Why `area-intellij`? I suppose the request comes from the Flutter plugin.

*@devoncarew commented on Oct 29, 2019, 7:26 PM UTC:*

Yeah, that's just a temporary marker to get this issue off the un-triaged queue. This issue should be moved to the flutter/flutter-intellij repo; we hope to re-enable the bot to help us do that soon.

*@alexander-doroshko commented on Jan 10, 2020, 10:11 AM UTC:*

@devoncarew Move to flutter-intellij?

title: we should only pass absolute file paths to `flutter.setSubscriptions`
